The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	Bareilly, Aug. 8 (PTI): As many as 43 monkeys were poisoned to death at a village here by seven people who have been arrested, police said today.          
	The arrested persons have admitted to having killed the monkeys as they were destroying crops and attacking people, superintendent of police Rakesh Jolly said. Animal rights activist Maneka Gandhi has demanded stringent action against those arrested.                   
	New Delhi (PTI): The income-tax department has been criticised by Delhi High Court for filing needless appeals against tax tribunal decisions. A bench of Chief Justice Dipak Misra and Justice Manmohan said that the courts time should not be wasted by filing needless litigations.                  
	New Delhi (PTI): Ahead of the Commonwealth Games, Delhi will get a police station exclusively for foreign tourists with its personnel having a good command over English. The police station will come up in central Delhis Paharganj, an official said.                   
	Bundi, Rajasthan (PTI): A local court on Sunday rejected a petition charging Gujarat chief minister Narendra Modi with making derogatory remarks against Jawaharlal Nehru. Charmesh Sharma, a Youth Congress state secretary, had filed the petition.                  
	New Delhi (PTI): Delhi has registered 274 cases of murder in the first six months of this year compared with 254 during the same period last year and 259 in 2008 although the police strength was raised by over 22,000 men since 2007.                                                                                                                                              
